704735f-a.title: Brooklyn: Halsey Street - Wilson Avenue
704735f-a.text:
(1)
Halsey Street, west side, south of Wilson Ave., showing the Halsey Street Presbyterian Church, which was formerly known as the Gerwan Evangelist Church.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
(2)
The same, showing a closer view of the ckurck from the opposite
direction.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704737f-c.title: Brooklyn: Halsey Street - Wilson Avenue
704737f-c.text:
(1)
Halsey Street, west side, between Wilson and Khickerbocker Aves.
A view of the Irving Square Park.
1920.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing the northern end of the Park.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, looking southward. This block bounded by Weirfield and Halsey Streets and Wilson and Enickerbocker Aves., on the west, east, south and north respectively, was owned in 1869 by J. H. Bond.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
